original: Cronqvist, Gustav Knut, leg. läkare, Västervik, f. 13/1/09 i Landskrona av fanj. Sigfrid C. o. Anna Beata Persson. G. 42 m. Dera Lundgren. Barn: Kerstin Margareta f. 43, Brita Desideria 44. — Stud:ex. i Landskrona 28, med. kand. v. univ. i Lund 33 o. med. lic. där 39. E. o. andre läk. v. S:ta Gertruds sjukh. i Västervik 42-46, andre läk. sed. 47.
translated: Cronqvist, Gustav Knut, certified physician, Västervik, born January 13th, 1909 in Landskrona to Sergeant Sigfrid C. and Anna Beata Persson. Married in 1942 to Dera Lundgren. Children: Kerstin Margareta born in 1943, Brita Desideria born in 1944. He completed his high school education in Landskrona in 1928, obtained a Bachelor's degree in medicine at Lund University in 1933, and a medical license in 1939. He worked as a resident physician at S:ta Gertruds Hospital in Västervik from 1942-1946, then as an attending physician starting in 1947.
